<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> PREDICTION:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
After I explain how things work and their consequences, there will be TWO bugs.  The first prevents someone from levitating when a combo-buff overwrites them, because of the way levitation is coded.<br>
<br>
Because this bug <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>harms</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> players, it will not be fixed.<br>
<br>
However, the second bug allows players to levitate in zone where levitation has been disallowed, such as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Velketor's Labyrinth, The Hole, Siren's Grotto,</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> etc.<br>
<br>
Because this second bug <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>benefits</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> players, it will be fixed within a few patches.<br>
<br>
The first effect has to with the code for levitate.  There is an ON/OFF flag for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Levitate</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  You would expect that when a buff whose effect includes <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Levitate</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> takes effect, it would set LEVITATE = ON.  It does not.  Instead, it TOGGLES LEVITATE.  If it was off, it is now on, and vice versa.<br>
<br>
To demonstrate this, remove all buffs, and cast <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Levitate</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> on yourself.  You are now levitating.  Now ask someone to cast either <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Dead Man Floating</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spirit of Eagle</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> on you.  It will overwrite <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Levitate</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, but when the buff takes effect, it will TOGGLE LEVITATE.  Since levitate was already ON, levitate is now OFF, and you drop to the ground like a rock.<br>
<br>
Fixing this bug involves rewriting a fraction of a single line of C Code, the equivalent of altering <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>one</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> CPU instruction, but because it harms players, it has zero priority.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Levitation &quot;stacks&quot; with Spirit of the Eagle (buff icons are both up)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Not exactly.  There is a <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>second</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, much more complicated bug here.<br>
<br>
To demonstrate this second bug, stand outside a NO LEV zone, remove all buffs, and cast <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> See Invisible</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Levitate</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> on your self in that order.  You are floating.  Now ask someone to cast either <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Dead Man Floating</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spirit of Eagle</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> on you.  It will overwrite <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> See Invisible</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, but <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>not</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Levitate</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, so you will now have both icons.<br>
<br>
Now zone into <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Velketor's</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Siren's Grotto</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  The code that disables <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Levitate</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> will discover only the first buff, SOE or DMF, and remove it.  However, it will stop there, and not remove <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Levitation</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Now that you have successfully zoned into <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Siren's Grotto</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the ordinary buff check code comes into play.  It finds that you indeed have a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Levitation</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> buff on, toggles levitate, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> viola!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  You are now levitating in a NO LEV zone.<br>
<br>
Note that this second bug is much more complex, and involved many lines of code in several different functions: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> How Buffs are Overridden, How Buffs are Stripped at No Lev Zone Ins, How Buffs are restored at Upon Zone in</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Although this bug is much more complex, affects more lines of code than the first bug, and involves multiple interacting functions, because it benefits players, the bug fix will receive a high priority, and will be fixed within a few patches.<br>
<br>
